objects.text: Be careful to have enough fuel!
Killing an enemy gives fuel back.
You can still use powers and Shift though
They explode when you touch them.
Left/right click to use your powers.
Hold Space to Sprint, and tap wasd keys to conserve fuel
Lightly tap between 2-3 times per second
They pull players in on contact.
Take your time - they do not directly kill you.
You can get fuel from them.
Up and down, Red and blue.
You are in the enemy base now.
Get to the field at the end!
Press this button to open the door.
Sometimes, you have to avoid them.
Try to stay in normal gravity.
You need fuel, yet you need to go right.
You are familiar with Space right?
Consider this a basic skill test
After all, this is an optional map
They look like GravityUp, but they aren't
The other Half Flip it Up
Sometimes, you have to avoid them.
They Alter Your Gravity For 3 seconds
But if you touch another one the cooldown refreshes
They explode if you touch them
When you hit it, it bounces you in the direction of your controls.
They are immune to your abilities.
They expand when you get near them.
They drain or replenish your fuel
Maybe don't fall into the crevice nice time...
Their bodies are immune to abilities
You are faster in the air
You have passed the first test
This time, you escaped the Inferno.
Next time, you won't be so lucky.
The infernus is even more deadly than the inferno.
There is no way to escape it.
It is not too late to turn back.
uh oh... which way to go?
press o to see hidden outlines
Look closely to see the enemies...
Blocks can be used to create pixel art.
You have made it to the party!
